        <li><strong>Decision-making:</strong> By exploring different perspectives, Tarot can help you make more informed choices.</li>
        <li><strong>Problem-solving:</strong> Tarot readings can reveal hidden aspects of a situation and suggest new approaches.</li>
        <li><strong>Personal growth:</strong> The archetypal imagery of Tarot facilitates profound psychological insights.</li>
        <li><strong>Mindfulness:</strong> The ritual of a Tarot reading encourages presence and reflection.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="blog-section">
      <h2>Getting Started with Tarot</h2>
      <p>If you're new to Tarot, getting started might seem overwhelming, but it's easier than you might think:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Choose a deck:</strong> Select a deck that resonates with you visually and intuitively.</li>
        <li><strong>Familiarize yourself:</strong> Spend time with your cards, looking at the imagery and reading about their meanings.</li>
        <li><strong>Start simple:</strong> Begin with one-card daily draws to build your relationship with the cards.</li>
        <li><strong>Keep a journal:</strong> Record your readings and reflections to track your progress.</li>
        <li><strong>Trust your intuition:</strong> As you become more comfortable, let your instincts guide your interpretations.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>
    
